<h3 id="unique">unique</h3>

<p>For a range, remove consecutive duplicate elements. (Ex. { 2 2 3 3 4 4 4 3 } -&gt; { 2 3 4 3 ? ? ? ? } ) This is done by moving a valid element into the removed elementŌĆÖs spot. (The container size does not change.) YouŌĆÖll know where the updated range ends by checking where the returned iterator is. Order is not preserved, and the extra elements at the end of the range are in some valid state.</p>

