</ul>

<div class="language-cpp highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="n">std</span><span class="o">::</span><span class="n">vector</span><span class="o">&lt;</span><span class="kt">int</span><span class="o">&gt;</span> <span class="n">v</span><span class="p">{</span> <span class="mi">5</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">4</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">3</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">200</span> <span class="p">};</span>

<span class="n">std</span><span class="o">::</span><span class="n">vector</span><span class="o">&lt;</span><span class="kt">int</span><span class="o">&gt;::</span><span class="n">iterator</span> <span class="n">it</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">std</span><span class="o">::</span><span class="n">is_heap_until</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">v</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="n">begin</span><span class="p">(),</span> <span class="n">v</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="n">end</span><span class="p">());</span> <span class="c1">// Points to 200</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

<h1 id="min-and-max">Min and Max</h1>

<p>These algorithms are related to finding the minimum/maximum element in a range, or when comparing two items.</p>

<h3 id="min">min</h3>

<p>Compares two items and returns the smaller one.</p>

<ul>
  <li>Pass in two items (<code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">int</code>s, for example) as parameters.</li>
